<nav></nav>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is a very generous country for both local and international students in research. There are many different scholarships and project support available, especially for master&#8217;s and PhD level studies. When I first arrived, I didn&#8217;t know there were so many options, I was a bit overwhelmed during the application process, so in this article I will try to guide you from start to finish.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="research-scholarships-in-turkey-who-can-apply">Research Scholarships in Turkey: Who Can Apply?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Research grants in Turkey are generally aimed at students who meet a certain level of academic achievement. Many doors are also open for international students. In particular, the following groups can easily apply for scholarships:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Enrolled in a master&#8217;s or doctoral program in Turkey</li>



<li>Guest students participating in research exchange programs</li>



<li>Independent researchers without support from their home country</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The main criteria considered during applications include academic grade point average (GPA), originality of the research topic and detailed project plan.</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Application Requirement</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Academic Achievement</td>
<td>GPA above 3.00/4.GPA above 00</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Language Proficiency</td>
<td>Certificate of proficiency in English or Turkish</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Project Plan</td>
<td>Contain clear objectives and methodology</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These conditions may vary slightly in each institution, but this is the general framework.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more details, you can browse the relevant programs on the <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Road to Study website</a>.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="supports-provided-by-tubitak-and-other-institutions">Supports Provided by TUBITAKand Other Institutions</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey&#8217;s top research institution is <strong>TUBITAK (Scientific and Technological Research Council of Turkey)</strong>. TUBITAK provides both individual scholarships and major project support.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Other than these:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Special scholarships provided by the Council of Higher Education</li>



<li>Universities&#8217; own research funds (especially common in large foundation universities)</li>



<li>Joint projects with industrial organizations</li>



<li>Research grants from the European Union (such as Horizon Europe)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">also available.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Some Programs Provided by TUBITAK:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>2216 &#8211; Fellowship Program for Foreign Researchers</li>



<li>2210 &#8211; Graduate Scholarship Program</li>



<li>2232 &#8211; International Leading Researchers Program</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is very important to check the details of the grants and the current application deadlines on the <a href="https://tubitak.gov.tr/tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TUBITAK official website</a>, because sometimes the deadline can be over in a few weeks.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process-steps-to-consider">Application Process: Steps to Consider</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Every step is crucial when applying for a scholarship in Turkey. Even a small mistake can delay the process. I have prepared a step-by-step list to make your job easier:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Determine Your Research Topic:</strong> Choosing a specific and innovative topic is critical.</li>



<li><strong>Find an Advisor:</strong> Contact an academic advisor in Turkey in the field you want to study.</li>



<li><strong>Prepare Application Documents:</strong></li>



<li><strong>Apply Online:</strong> Upload your documents to the organization&#8217;s system.</li>



<li><strong>Prepare for Interviews:</strong> Some programs may also require an interview.</li>
</ol>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Document gathering takes the most time in this process. Especially details such as sworn translations should not be left to the last minute. While I was preparing my documents, I translated a few of them incorrectly, I realized at the last moment and corrected them; I recommend you to be careful too.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more tips and tricks on how to apply, check out <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Road to Study&#8217;s scholarship guide</a>.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">Developing a Project in Turkey: Tips for International Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">When developing a project in Turkey, it is a great advantage to consider not only the academic world, but also the business world and industry. The most important thing I learned while writing a project was to focus on practice rather than theory.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are a few tips for developing projects in Turkey:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Choose a real issue:</strong> Issues that address the local dynamics and needs of Turkey increase the chances of finding support.</li>



<li><strong>Keep in constant contact with your advisor:</strong> The experience of your academic advisor can take your project to a much more professional level.</li>



<li><strong>Research funding sources well:</strong> In addition to TUBITAK, institutions such as KOSGEB also provide project-based support (<a class="" href="https://www.kosgeb.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Information about KOSGEB supports</a>).</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Projects in areas such as technology, energy, agriculture and health are very popular in Turkey at the moment. If you go into one of these fields, you have a much better chance of both acceptance and additional funding.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="opportunities-and-challenges-you-may-encounter-in-turkey-while-doing-research">Opportunities and Challenges You May Encounter in Turkey While Doing Research</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Doing research in Turkey sounds exciting at first (and it is), but obviously you have to be prepared for some challenges. When I first arrived, I realized that the laboratory infrastructure differs in some universities, so it is important to research beforehand.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Opportunities:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>International collaborations and Erasmus+ research exchange programs</li>



<li>A dynamic and young academic environment</li>



<li>Developing R&amp;D centers and technoparks</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Challenges:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Limited laboratory facilities in some universities</li>



<li>Slow progress of bureaucratic procedures at times</li>



<li>Tongue barrier (especially in technical documents)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These may seem daunting, but with the right preparation and patience, they can all be overcome. And a little advice: Every city in Turkey has a different culture. In big cities like Istanbul, academic opportunities are vast, while in smaller cities life is quieter and easier to focus.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="suggestions-for-a-successful-scholarship-application">Suggestions for a Successful Scholarship Application</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Finally, we come to the most important part: What do you have to do to get the scholarship? </p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Develop an original project idea:</strong> Instead of stereotypes, present an innovative perspective.</li>



<li><strong>Prepare complete documents:</strong> Missing documents may result in automatic rejection of the application.</li>



<li><strong>Pay attention to timing:</strong> Scholarship applications in Turkey are usually open at certain times of the year. Start preparing at least 3 months in advance to avoid missing the application period.</li>



<li><strong>Personalize your motivational letter:</strong> Instead of standard sentences, answer the questions &#8220;why this project, why Turkey?&#8221; in a sincere way.</li>



<li><strong>Aim for small grants first:</strong> Winning small grants before applying for big scholarships can be a serious boost to your CV.</li>
</ul>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h1 class="wp-block-heading" id="start-your-research-dream-in-turkey-now">Start Your Research Dream in Turkey Now!</h1>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The opportunities for research and project development in Turkey are much wider than you think. All you have to do is take the right steps and don&#8217;t give up. If you still have questions or are wondering which scholarship program is right for you, you can contact <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a> now.<br>Now is the time to take action for your dreams!</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-08-04T10:48:17Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T18:37:29Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/research-fellowships-and-project-support-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Research fellowships and project funding opportunities in Turkey","title":"research-fellowships-and-project-support-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'turkey-research-scholarships' );
