<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As a graduate student, I had hundreds of questions when I was researching scholarship options in Turkey. Especially things like can I get a state scholarship, who qualifies for it. If you are in the same situation, you are in the right place.<br>Here I will explain in detail both government supports and private opportunities.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="is-there-a-state-scholarship-for-graduate-students-in-turkey">Is there a State Scholarship for Graduate Students in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, the government offers direct and indirect scholarships to graduate students. The most well-known programs are YTB Turkey Scholarships and KYK scholarships.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="general-information-about-ytb-turkey-scholarships">General Information About YTB Turkey Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Provided by the Presidency for Turks Abroad and Related Communities (YTB), <a href="https://ytb.gov.tr/daireler/uluslararasi-ogrenciler" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turkey Scholarships </a>open doors to students from all over the world.<br>This scholarship provides monthly financial support, accommodation, health insurance and even Turkish preparatory education to graduate students.<br></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are thinking of applying for YTB scholarships, be sure to check RoadtoStudy&#8217;s <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/ytb-burslari-basvuru/" data-type="link" data-id="https://roadtostudy.com/ytb-burslari-basvuru/">YTB Scholarships: Be sure to review the content of Who Can Apply, How to Apply.</a></p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="kyk-scholarship-and-loan-what-it-offers-for-graduate-students">KYK Scholarship and Loan: What It Offers for Graduate Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KYK (Credit and Dormitories Institution) provides scholarships and student loans not only to undergraduate students but also to graduate students.<br>After applying for a graduate scholarship, KYK can offer you a scholarship or loan directly according to your success and income criteria.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The loan has to be repaid, while the scholarship is completely free of charge.<br>From my own experience, don&#8217;t be upset if you get a loan. Because the payment terms are quite flexible after graduation.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="yuksek-lisans-ogrencileri-ne-kadar-burs-aliyor">


<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">How Much Scholarship Do Graduate Students Get?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Current scholarship amounts available from various sources in Turkey are as follows:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Scholarship Type</th>
<th>Monthly Amount (USD, 2025)</th>
<th>Application Time</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>YTB Turkey Scholarship</td>
<td>~158 USD</td>
<td>January-February</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>KYK Scholarship</td>
<td>~79 USD</td>
<td>October-November</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>TÜBİTAK 2210-A</td>
<td>~$197 USD</td>
<td>Year-Long (Semester-long)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>University Scholarships</td>
<td>~$66 &#8211; 158 USD</td>
<td>Variates by University</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="state-scholarships-amounts-kyk-ytb-tubitak">State Scholarships Amounts (KYK, YTB, TÜBİTAK )</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For example, as of 2025, the KYK master&#8217;s scholarship is around <strong>105 USD</strong>.<br>YTB Turkey Scholarships can go up to <strong>132 USD</strong> for master&#8217;s students and <strong>171 USD</strong> for PhD students.<br>Trivate and University Based Scholarships</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some universities also offer scholarships to graduate students from their own resources.<br>For example, institutions such as Boğaziçi University and Sabancı University offer scholarships based on academic achievement.<br>These scholarships are usually between 25% and 100% tuition waivers.<br>Some schools also provide meal cards or dormitory support.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For detailed university-based scholarship information, you can visit my <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Universities and Departments in Turkey</a> page.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="kyk-graduate-scholarship-requirements-and-application-process">KYK Graduate Scholarship Requirements and Application Process</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to get a KYK scholarship, you have to fulfill certain requirements.<br>I went through the process from start to finish in my own application and found that paying attention to a few small details made all the difference.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="who-can-apply">Who can apply?</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Citizens of the Republic of Turkey</li>



<li>New enrollees in a graduate program</li>



<li>Successful completion of undergraduate studies</li>



<li>Those with low income (family declaration is important)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The KYK also takes into account the order of success and academic performance.<br>If you graduated from a university ranked in the top 100, your chances are slightly higher.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-dates-and-required-documents">Application Dates and Required Documents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">KYK scholarship applications are usually opened every year in <strong>October-November</strong>.<br>Documents required for application:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Photocopy of ID</li>



<li>Photocopy of bachelor&#8217;s degree</li>



<li>Master&#8217;s degree acceptance certificate</li>



<li>Family income declaration (easily available via e-Government)</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications are made entirely through e-Government, no mail or face-to-face transactions are made.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">I recommend that you check <a href="https://kygm.gsb.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">KYK&#8217;s official announcement page</a><a class="">i</a> regularly so as not to miss the application dates.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-graduate-scholarship-how-many-points-does-it-close-with">TÜBİTAK Graduate Scholarship: How many points does it close with?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the scholarships that those aiming for an academic career in Turkey should definitely consider is the TÜBİTAK graduate scholarships.<br>Particularly 2210-A and 2210-B programs support academic studies.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="tubitak-2210-a-and-2210-b-programs">TÜBİTAK 2210-A and 2210-B Programs</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The TÜBİTAK 2210-A program is a scholarship for graduate students in the fields of basic sciences, engineering, health and social sciences.<br>2210-B provides support for students working on industry-oriented projects.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Application requirements include:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Pursuing a full-time master&#8217;s degree in Turkey</li>



<li>High academic achievement (undergraduate GPA usually above 3.00/4.00)</li>



<li>Presenting a scientific work plan</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are criteria such as <br>You should definitely check <a href="https://tubitak.gov.tr/tr/burslar/lisansustu/egitim-burs-programlari/2210-yurt-ici-yuksek-lisans-burs-programlari" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TÜBİTAK &#8216;s official website</a> for application and detailed information.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="base-points-in-recent-years">Base Points in Recent Years</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In recent years, the average closing scores for TÜBİTAK 2210-A scholarships have been as follows:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th>Year</th><th>Average Closing Grade (Undergraduate)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>2022</td><td>3.15 / 4.00</td></tr><tr><td>2023</td><td>3.05 / 4.00</td></tr><tr><td>2024</td><td>3.10 / 4.00</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">This means that if your GPA is around 3.00 and you have a good project proposal, your chances are quite high.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarship-opportunities-provided-by-universities-in-turkey">Scholarship Opportunities Provided by Universities in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In addition to state scholarships, many universities in Turkey offer special scholarships for graduate students.<br>Especially foundation universities offer serious support to attract talented students.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-universities-with-the-most-scholarships">The Universities with the Most Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some universities have really impressive scholarship policies.<br>For example:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Sabancı University</strong>: It offers scholarships from 25% to 100% based on merit and need.</li>



<li><strong>Koç University</strong>: It provides graduate students with full scholarships, health insurance and sometimes monthly living support.</li>



<li><strong>Bilkent University</strong>: It offers monthly scholarship + dormitory support based on academic achievement.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarships offered by these universities are often limited by availability, so applying early is critical.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-requirements-and-processes">Application Requirements and Processes</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To apply for university-based scholarships usually:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>letter of acceptance</li>



<li>Certificates of academic achievement</li>



<li>English proficiency (compulsory in some schools)</li>



<li>Interview process</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">necessary.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="tips-and-common-mistakes-for-scholarship-application">Tips and Common Mistakes for Scholarship Application</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Small mistakes when applying for a job can cause you to miss out on big opportunities.<br>Here are a few critical tips from experience:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="strengthening-the-application-file">Strengthening the Application File</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>When preparing your academic CV, be sure to include your projects and awards you have received.</li>



<li>Reference letters must be personal. A standard &#8220;successful student&#8221; letter does not work.</li>



<li>Make sure to have several people read your research plan or motivational letter and get feedback.</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="motivation-letter-and-reference-letters">Motivation Letter and Reference Letters</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarship institutions want to see not only your GPA, but also why you want to join this program and your future goals.<br>A friend of mine was rejected because her motivation letter was too superficial. Later, when he applied with a detailed letter, he was accepted.<br>It really makes a difference to give strong answers to the questions &#8220;why this department, why Turkey&#8221;.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="dont-postpone-your-dream-dont-miss-the-opportunity-of-a-scholarship-masters-degree-in-turkey">Don&#8217;t Postpone Your Dream: Don&#8217;t Miss the Opportunity of a Scholarship Master&#8217;s Degree in Turkey!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Graduate education opportunities in Turkey are increasing every year and scholarships are making this process more accessible.<br>Particularly state-sponsored programs such as YTB, KYK and TÜBİTAK offer serious support to graduate students.</p>


<p><a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com/">RoadtoStudy</a>, you can accelerate the process with the right scholarship and application strategy.</p>


