 Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/turkey-academic-merit-scholarships.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/turkey-academic-merit-scholarships.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"PhD scholarships and funding guide for Turkey","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/phd-scholarship-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/phd-scholarship-in-turkey/","name":"Turkish PhD Scholarship 2025: Big Opportunities Await You","datePublished":"2025-07-29T13:39:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:24:12+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/turkey-academic-merit-scholarships.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Turkish PhD Scholarship 2025: Big Opportunities Await You","keywords":"PhD","datePublished":"2025-07-29T13:39:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:24:12+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"If you&#039;re looking for a PhD scholarship in Turkiye, amazing opportunities await you in 2025. Learn about TUBITAK 2211-A and other support programs and apply now!","name":"Turkish PhD Scholarship 2025: Big Opportunities Await You","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/phd-scholarship-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/phd-scholarship-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/turkey-academic-merit-scholarships.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/phd-scholarship-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>If you are looking for a PhD scholarship</strong>, Turkey is the place for you! Doing a PhD in Turkey can be a great step for your academic career and life experience. But to be honest, the financial side is just as important as academic success. Fortunately, Turkey offers many scholarships and funding opportunities for foreign PhD students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><br>In this article, I&#8217;ve collected everything you need to know, from current scholarship amounts to application tips as of 2025. Let&#8217;s get started!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="doctoral-scholarship-options-in-turkey">Doctoral Scholarship Options in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many scholarship programs for <strong>international PhD students</strong> who want to study in Turkey, both government-funded and from the private sector.<br>I know from my own experience that finding the right scholarship can be a bit confusing at first. That&#8217;s why I&#8217;m simplifying the most important resources here.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="differences-for-domestic-and-international-students">Differences for Domestic and International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are some fundamental differences in the scholarship system in Turkey between local and foreign students.<br>For example, <strong>YOK Scholarships</strong> and <strong>TÜBİTAK grants</strong> are open to both Turkish and foreign students, while some private foundation scholarships are only available to students from certain countries.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Main Scholarship Options:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong><strong>TÜBİTAK </strong>2211-A Domestic PhD Scholarship Program</strong></li>



<li><strong>Turkey Scholarships</strong> (provided by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs)</li>



<li><strong>University Based Scholarships</strong> (Ex: Boğaziçi University Research Grants)</li>



<li><strong>Private Foundation and Association Scholarships</strong> (such as TEV, Vehbi Koç Foundation)</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-you-need-to-know-in-the-application-process">What You Need to Know in the Application Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The following documents are usually requested during the application process:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Bachelor&#8217;s and master&#8217;s degrees</li>



<li>Foreign language proficiency certificate (IELTS/TOEFL)</li>



<li>Research proposal</li>



<li>Letters of reference</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most scholarship programs in Turkey conduct online applications and usually open in the first quarter of the year. I recommend that you start collecting your documents early in preparation.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
