<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="sources-of-additional-funding-for-doctoral-students">Sources of Additional Funding for Doctoral Students</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, you can earn income in different ways, not only through traditional scholarship programs. Especially for PhD students, research projects and part-time jobs are good sources of additional finance.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="research-project-assistant-ra">Research Project Assistant (RA)</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most Turkish universities run large-scale scientific projects and need research assistants to work on them.<br>Many international students earn a monthly income from these projects while continuing their studies. In many cases, these assignments are also part of an official PhD fellowship and provide a substantial salary.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Doctoral students working in an RA position usually:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Writes projects and analyzes data</li>



<li>Participates in laboratory studies</li>



<li>Takes part in conference organizations</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you win this kind of position, you also have the chance to gain an academic environment.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="work-permissions-and-part-time-options">Work Permissions and Part-Time Options</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey allows student visa holders to work part-time for limited hours.<br>It is easier to find work, especially on university campuses or in technology development zones. However, you must obtain the relevant permit before you start working.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These jobs are usually:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Academic assistantship</li>



<li>Librarian</li>



<li>Part-time positions in software and R&amp;D companies</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">So you don&#8217;t have to settle for just a PhD scholarship; you can easily increase your monthly income by taking advantage of these opportunities.</p>


