<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><br>In this article, I&#8217;ve collected everything you need to know, from current scholarship amounts to application tips as of 2025. Let&#8217;s get started!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="doctoral-scholarship-options-in-turkey">Doctoral Scholarship Options in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many scholarship programs for <strong>international PhD students</strong> who want to study in Turkey, both government-funded and from the private sector.<br>I know from my own experience that finding the right scholarship can be a bit confusing at first. That&#8217;s why I&#8217;m simplifying the most important resources here.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="differences-for-domestic-and-international-students">Differences for Domestic and International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are some fundamental differences in the scholarship system in Turkey between local and foreign students.<br>For example, <strong>YOK Scholarships</strong> and <strong>TÜBİTAK grants</strong> are open to both Turkish and foreign students, while some private foundation scholarships are only available to students from certain countries.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Main Scholarship Options:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong><strong>TÜBİTAK </strong>2211-A Domestic PhD Scholarship Program</strong></li>



<li><strong>Turkey Scholarships</strong> (provided by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs)</li>



<li><strong>University Based Scholarships</strong> (Ex: Boğaziçi University Research Grants)</li>



<li><strong>Private Foundation and Association Scholarships</strong> (such as TEV, Vehbi Koç Foundation)</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-you-need-to-know-in-the-application-process">What You Need to Know in the Application Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The following documents are usually requested during the application process:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Bachelor&#8217;s and master&#8217;s degrees</li>



<li>Foreign language proficiency certificate (IELTS/TOEFL)</li>



<li>Research proposal</li>



<li>Letters of reference</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most scholarship programs in Turkey conduct online applications and usually open in the first quarter of the year. I recommend that you start collecting your documents early in preparation.</p>


