<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to do an exchange in Turkey, knowing about Erasmus+ scholarships will make your job easier. Now let&#8217;s get into the details.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<h2 id="erasmus-programi-what-is-and-who-can-apply" class="wp-block-heading"> </h2>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">What is the Erasmus+ Program and Who Can Apply?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Erasmus+ is an education and youth program supported by the European Union. Its aim is to enable students from different countries to engage in cultural and academic exchange with each other. By 2025, more than 100 universities in Turkey will open their doors to international students under <strong>Erasmus</strong> agreements.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">So who can benefit from <strong>Erasmus in Turkey</strong></p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more comprehensive information about the Erasmus+ program, you can also take a look at our <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-degisim-programlari-erasmus-mevlana-farabi/">What is the Erasmus+ Program and Who Can Apply? </a> guide.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="advantages-of-studying-with-erasmus-scholarships-in-turkey">Advantages of Studying with Erasmus+ Scholarships in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey offers many advantages for Erasmus+ scholars. While I was studying in Istanbul, I got to know different cultures and lived at much more affordable costs. Here are some of the most important advantages:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Advantages</strong></th>
<th><strong>Descriptions</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Low Cost of Living</strong></td>
<td>Cheaper accommodation, transportation, and food compared to European countries.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Cultural Richness</strong></td>
<td>Historical sites, diverse food culture, and festivals.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Advanced Universities</strong></td>
<td>Many universities in Turkey are ranked among the world’s top institutions.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Wide Social Life</strong></td>
<td>Student clubs, sports activities, and vibrant social events are abundant.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can also follow the latest developments on the <a>Turkish National Agency Erasmus+ Page</a> for official information.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="erasmus-application-process-step-by-step-guide">Erasmus+ Application Process: Step-by-Step Guide</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>If you are dreaming of Erasmus</strong> in Turkey, the application process can be a bit daunting at first. At first, I didn&#8217;t know which document to submit and where to submit it, and I had to collect my documents at the last minute. So I would like to explain the process to you step by step.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Steps to follow to apply for Erasmus</strong> in Turkey:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Find out the application dates from your university&#8217;s Erasmus Coordination Office.</li>



<li>Prepare the necessary documents (CV, letter of intent, transcript, etc.).</li>



<li>Fill out the online application form completely.</li>



<li>Take the language test set by the university (usually in English or the language of instruction).</li>



<li>Wait for the selection results and start the placement process when you are accepted.</li>
</ol>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>The Erasmus</strong> application process in Turkey requires serious attention to ensure that documents are complete and that deadlines are not missed. </p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are looking for more detailed information, you can also access the official guidelines provided by the European Commission through the <a class="" href="https://erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Erasmus+ Application Guide</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="which-documents-are-required-erasmus-application-tips">Which Documents Are Required? Erasmus+ Application Tips</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Preparing the correct and complete documents for the Erasmus+ application is the most critical part of the process. I once wrote and sent my letter of intent on the last night, don&#8217;t be like me!</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are the key documents:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Application Form</strong> (obtained from the Erasmus office of the university)</li>



<li><strong>Updated Transcript</strong></li>



<li><strong>Language Proficiency Certificate</strong> (for English or language of instruction)</li>



<li><strong>Motivational Letter</strong></li>



<li><strong>CV (Curriculum Vitae)</strong></li>



<li><strong>Student Certificate</strong></li>



<li><strong>Passport Photocopy</strong></li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Tips:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Write your motivational letter in an original and personal way. Avoid clichés.</li>



<li>Showcase your Erasmus-related experiences in your CV.</li>



<li>Prepare the documents a few weeks before the application date if possible.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In addition, you can find additional information for international students interested in studying in Turkey on the <a class="" href="https://studyinturkey.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Student Exchange Programs and Credit Transfer in Turkey</a> page.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="life-in-turkey-with-erasmus-scholarship-experiences-and-advices">Life in Turkey with Erasmus+ Scholarship: Experiences and Advices</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Living in Turkey on an Erasmus</strong> scholarship is an adventure in itself. Everything from the food to the public transportation is worth the experience.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>A few tips on living in Turkey:</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Transportation:</strong> You can travel very cheaply with city transportation cards (Istanbulkart, AnkaraKart). In particular, our guide to <a>Transportation Costs and Public Transportation Cards in Turkey</a> will help you plan your budget.</li>



<li><strong>Housing:</strong> Student dormitories, apartments and shared houses are the most preferred options. When looking for a house, it is very important which neighborhood you will live in; on this subject <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Student Houses in Turkey: Neighborhood Selection and Safety</a>, be sure to read our article.</li>



<li><strong>Daily Life:</strong> You can find fresh and cheap fruits and vegetables in the markets. It is normal to negotiate!</li>



<li><strong>Cultural Activities:</strong> Special discounts are offered for international students at theaters, concerts and exhibitions.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>To make the most of your Erasmus</strong> experience in Turkey, be open to the local culture and take every opportunity to experience new things.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="take-action-now-realize-your-dream-in-turkey">Take Action Now: Realize Your Dream in Turkey!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Studying in Turkey with an Erasmus+ scholarship can change not only your academic career but also your outlook on life. Cultural richness, warm human relations and a globally relevant experience await you.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Application periods are filling up fast, so it&#8217;s important that you take steps before you miss out.<br>If you still have questions or would like support with the application process, the <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">RoadToStudy</a> team is always ready to help you.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Act now and make your dream of education a reality in Turkey!</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How can I get an Erasmus scholarship?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Apply through your university’s Erasmus office, meet academic and language requirements, submit a motivation letter, and secure a nomination for the Erasmus+ program.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Can you do Erasmus as an international student?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, international students at Erasmus+ program or partner universities can participate if enrolled in a degree program and meet eligibility criteria.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to get a full scholarship for international students?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Apply for scholarships like Türkiye Scholarships or Erasmus+ via university portals, submit strong academic records, essays, and meet specific eligibility criteria.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Who can apply for an Erasmus scholarship?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students enrolled at Erasmus+ program or partner universities, with good academic standing, language proficiency, and a nomination from their home institution.</p>



