<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Presidency for Turks Abroad and Related Communities (YTB) provides scholarships to thousands of students every year to learn Turkish. The scholarship usually includes a year-long intensive Turkish preparatory program, and applicants are referred to language centers at universities across Turkey.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Who can apply for YTB Scholarship?</strong></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>International students pursuing undergraduate, graduate or doctoral studies</li>



<li>Candidates under the age of 25 with an academic success average above 70%</li>



<li>Who have not received a government scholarship in Turkey before</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="ankara-university-tomer-and-other-institutions">Ankara University TOMER and Other Institutions</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a class="" href="https://tomer.ankara.edu.tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TOMER (Turkish and Foreign Language Application and Research Center)</a> is one of the most established language teaching centers in Turkey. Ankara University TOMER in particular stands out with its high-quality teaching staff and branches across Turkey. Registrations usually open at the beginning of the semester and quotas can fill up quickly. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiye-egitim-dili-secimi/" data-type="post" data-id="2386">The registration guides are very useful for students who want to get detailed information about TOMER courses.</a></p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="foreign-language-education-in-turkey-english-arabic-and-more">Foreign Language Education in Turkey: English, Arabic and More</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Yes, not everyone has to learn Turkish. There are many institutions and universities in Turkey where you can study in different languages such as English, French, German or even Korean. Moreover, there are scholarship opportunities in these fields as well.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="foreign-language-departments-in-universities">Foreign Language Departments in Universities</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many Turkish universities offer English-major programs in departments such as English Language Teaching, Translation and Interpreting or Linguistics. Boğaziçi University, Hacettepe University and Istanbul University stand out in these fields. Some universities offer special scholarships for international students who choose these departments.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="meb-and-other-institutions-foreign-language-scholarships">MEB and Other Institutions&#8217; Foreign Language Scholarships</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Thanks to scholarship programs run by the Ministry of National Education through the <a class="" href="https://abdigm.meb.gov.tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Directorate General for EU and Foreign Relations</a>, students can study in English, Arabic and other languages in Turkey. These scholarships are usually:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Open to at least 4th year undergraduate students</li>



<li>A minimum score of 50 is required from exams such as TOEFL, IELTS or YDS</li>



<li>Fixed monthly scholarship includes accommodation and tuition support</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Turkish Language Association also offers postgraduate scholarships for social sciences students. These programs are a good resource for students who want to improve their academic language proficiency.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-for-language-scholarships-who-can-benefit-how-to-apply">Application for Language Scholarships: Who Can Benefit, How to Apply?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The process of applying for language scholarships can often seem complicated, but if you take it step by step, it can be very manageable. The important thing is to understand the conditions and not to miss the calendars.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-requirements-and-required-documents">Application Requirements and Required Documents</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In general, each scholarship program has different requirements, but there are some common ones:</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Documents Required for Application:</strong></p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Document Name</th>
<th>Required?</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<tr>
<td>Passport or ID</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>A valid and legible document</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Transcript</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>A document showing academic achievement</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Language Proficiency Certificate</td>
<td>Required</td>
<td>TOEFL, YDS, IELTS etc. (for some scholarships)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Letter of Intent</td>
<td>Often</td>
<td>You should explain why you want to apply</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Letter of Reference</td>
<td>Often</td>
<td>Academic or professional references</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="online-application-platforms-and-calendar">Online Application Platforms and Calendar</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarship applications are usually made through online platforms. Application periods during the year are usually concentrated in February and June.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Tips:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Prepare your documents in PDF format</li>



<li>Current and white background of the photo</li>



<li>Missing information on application forms</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="experiences-of-students-taking-language-education-in-turkey">Experiences of Students Taking Language Education in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It may be all well and good in theory, but real experiences are always the most valuable source of knowledge. What many international students who study languages in Turkey have in common is that this is the first time they have been exposed to cultural diversity in such an intense way.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="cultural-adaptation-process">Cultural Adaptation Process</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Adapting to a new country is not easy. The first few weeks are a bit difficult for everyone: new food, different ways of communicating, even gestures and facial expressions change. But don&#8217;t worry, especially in university preparatory classes or language centers such as TOMER, there is a supportive environment as most students go through a similar process.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Universities often organize an &#8220;orientation week&#8221; for foreign students. In this process, you both get to know the campus and have the opportunity to make new friends.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="language-learning-challenges-and-tips">Language Learning Challenges and Tips</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the most common challenges is the lack of speaking practice. No matter how many lessons you take, the language doesn&#8217;t really sink in until you speak it on the street. That&#8217;s why it helps so much to join volunteer communities, sign up for language exchange groups or dare to have simple conversations.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Tips:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Visit local markets, try to chat with vendors</li>



<li>Watch Turkish content on social media platforms</li>



<li>Get involved in the &#8220;Language Partner&#8221; system on campus</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="which-city-is-more-suitable-istanbul-ankara-and-izmir-comparison">Which City is More Suitable? Istanbul, Ankara and Izmir Comparison</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">City choice is not only about where to study a language, but also about what kind of lifestyle you want to have. Each of the major cities in Turkey offers its own unique advantages.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="education-quality-and-language-school-options">Education Quality and Language School Options</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Istanbul</strong>, Turkey&#8217;s cultural capital, has the largest number of language schools and private courses. Institutions such as Boğaziçi, Istanbul University and Sabancı University are particularly strong in language education.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Ankara</strong> is mostly the center of state institutions. <a class="" href="https://tomer.ankara.edu.tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ankara University TOMER</a> is located here and there is a serious academic environment.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Izmir</strong> attracts attention with its warm climate and more relaxed pace of life. Ege University&#8217;s language programs are especially preferred.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="cost-of-living-and-social-opportunities">Cost of Living and Social Opportunities</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The following table summarizes the cost of living and amenities in the three major cities:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>City</th>
<th>Social Facilities</th>
<th>Easy Transportation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Istanbul</td>
<td>Very diverse</td>
<td>Dense but developed</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Ankara</td>
<td>Medium</td>
<td>Easy and systematic</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Izmir</td>
<td>Easy and friendly</td>
<td>Easy and economical</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Istanbul is more expensive but unique in terms of cultural diversity. Ankara is calmer and more academic, while Izmir is a city with a bit of a vacation atmosphere.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="pros-and-cons-of-scholarship-language-education">Pros and Cons of Scholarship Language Education</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Every opportunity comes with its challenges. So is studying languages with a scholarship. I wanted to write this section honestly because you need to know not only the advantages but also the realities that await you.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The support offered by language scholarships in Turkey varies from program to program, but generally includes:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Free state dormitory or accommodation support</strong></li>



<li><strong>Health insurance</strong></li>



<li><strong>Flight ticket round-trip (for some programs)</strong></li>



<li><strong>1 year of free Turkish education (in programs such as YTB)</strong></li>
</ul>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<h2>Take One Step Closer to Your Dream Education: Apply Now</h2>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It may sound difficult to study languages in Turkey with a scholarship, but it is actually much easier with the right information and timely application. Successful students always say the same thing: &#8220;I&#8217;m glad I tried.&#8221; Don&#8217;t be late to start this process.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="guide-resources-and-tips">Guide Resources and Tips</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><a class="" href="https://www.ytb.gov.tr" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Follow the current application dates on YTB official website</a></li>



<li>Check universities&#8217; TOMER pages regularly</li>



<li><a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a> for one-to-one counseling</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="dont-miss-the-deadline">Don&#8217;t Miss the Deadline</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most scholarship programs accept applications once a year and applications usually close between <strong>February and April</strong>. Prepare your documents in advance and don&#8217;t forget to check your e-mail box regularly.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-07-29T10:47:24Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T19:24:08Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/language-education-scholarships-in-turkey-turkish-and-other-languages.webp","alt":"Language education scholarships in Turkey for Turkish and other languages","title":"language-education-scholarships-in-turkey-turkish-and-other-languages"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'turkey-language-education-scholarships' );
