lternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarship-opportunities-for-disabled-foreign-students-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarship-opportunities-for-disabled-foreign-students-in-turkey.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"Scholarship opportunities for disabled foreign students in Turkey","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/disabled-students-scholarship-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/disabled-students-scholarship-turkey/","name":"Scholarships for Disabled Students in Turkey","datePublished":"2025-08-04T14:44:15+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:23:05+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarship-opportunities-for-disabled-foreign-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Scholarships for Disabled Students in Turkey","keywords":"Disabled Students","datePublished":"2025-08-04T14:44:15+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:23:05+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Learn about scholarship opportunities in Turkey for international disabled students. Discover government, university and foundation support. Apply now!","name":"Scholarships for Disabled Students in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/disabled-students-scholarship-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/disabled-students-scholarship-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarship-opportunities-for-disabled-foreign-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/disabled-students-scholarship-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is a country that values equal access to education for students with disabilities. If you are an international student with disabilities, you can apply for various scholarships offered by both the state and universities and foundations in Turkey.turkey is a country that values equal access to education for students with disabilities.s a country that values equal access to education for students with disabilitboth the</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">At first, some students think that these supports are only for Turkish citizens, but this is not the case. In recent years, especially the <em>Turkey Scholarships</em> program and special quotas of universities have opened doors for foreign disabled students.</p>


<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">


<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Universities are taking serious steps towards physical accessibility. There are many applications such as stair-free entrances, elevator systems and special education technologies. For detailed accessibility practices, be sure to check our article titled <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">Accessibility for Students with Disabilities in Turkey</a>.</p>
</blockquote>


</blockquote>
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="scholarships-offered-by-the-state-and-universities">Scholarships Offered by the State and Universities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey Scholarships program is one of the leading scholarships provided by the government. This program provides full scholarships to international students at different levels (undergraduate, graduate, doctoral). Although there is no special quota for students with disabilities, additional support can be requested by reporting the health status during the application process.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some state and foundation universities also offer special scholarships or services for students with disabilities.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="comparative-scholarship-table">Comparative Scholarship Table</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Below is a brief comparison of a few featured scholarships:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Scholarship Name</th>
<th>Who Can Apply?</th>
<th>Scope</th>
<th>Application Period</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Turkey Scholarships</td>
<td>All foreign students</td>
<td>Monthly scholarship, accommodation, health</td>
<td>January &#8211; February</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Boğaziçi University Scholarship</td>
<td>Successful disabled foreign students</td>
<td>Tuition fee, food, housing</td>
<td>After university entrance</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Ankara University Accessibility Scholarship</td>
<td>Foreign students with disabilities</td>
<td>Partial scholarship, technical support</td>
<td>Student affairs period</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more details, you can visit the official website of <a class="" href="https://www.turkiyeburslari.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turkey Scholarships</a>.</p>


</blockquote>
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="additional-support-from-foundations-and-civil-society-organizations">Additional Support from Foundations and Civil Society Organizations</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are other sources besides the state for disabled foreign students studying in Turkey. Some large foundations and non-governmental organizations open scholarship programs especially for disadvantaged groups. Foreigners are among the students who apply for these scholarships every year.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="supporting-institutions">Supporting Institutions</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Darüşşafaka Society</strong>: It can offer housing and education scholarships to disabled and underprivileged students. Although Turkish students are usually prioritized, foreign students can also be included in some projects.</li>



<li><strong>TEGV (Educational Volunteers Foundation of Turkey)</strong>: Although it works mostly at the primary education level, it has collaborations that support university scholarship programs.</li>



<li><strong>Support from the Ministry of Family and Social Services</strong>: For foreign students studying in Turkey, indirect support (technical equipment, transportation assistance) can play a role, although not directly.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">It is very important to contact these organizations and find out which programs are open to international students. You can facilitate this process by getting support from <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


