ription":"Scholarship programs for refugees and asylum seekers in Turkey, application conditions and guidance are waiting for you. Apply now!","name":"Scholarship for Refugee and Asylum seekers Students in Turkey","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarships-for-refugees-and-asylum-seekers-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarships-for-refugees-and-asylum-seekers-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarship-programs-for-refugee-and-asylum-seeker-students-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/scholarships-for-refugees-and-asylum-seekers-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">What does it mean to be a refugee and asylum seeker in Turkey?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Being a refugee or asylum seeker in Turkey often means not only living in a new country, but also resetting the past and building the future from scratch. Thousands of young people who left their countries due to war, economic crisis or political reasons want to continue their education with the hope of building a new life in Turkey. </p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="basic-difficulties-in-access-to-the-right-to-education">Basic Difficulties in Access to the Right to Education</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Refugee and asylum-seeking students in Turkey often fall behind in accessing university education due to language barriers, lack of documentation and financial constraints. Some students cannot enroll because it takes too long for their high school diplomas to be recognized. Others have to support their families, which makes regular attendance impossible.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="psychological-reflections-of-being-a-student-with-refugee-status">Psychological Reflections of Being a Student with Refugee Status</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For many students who have been separated from their families, traumatized by war, or who have experienced serious difficulties during the migration process, studying in Turkey is also a psychological reconstruction process. Therefore, scholarship programs are not only financial support, but also a door of hope.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="turkey-scholarships-the-most-comprehensive-government-program">Turkey Scholarships: The Most Comprehensive Government Program</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the most well-known support programs for refugee and asylum-seeking students in Turkey is undoubtedly Turkey Scholarships. This state-sponsored system opens the door to foreign students who want to study at both undergraduate and graduate level. Quotas are reserved especially for students with refugee status.</p>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="turkiye-burslari-nedir-ve-kimler-basvurabilir">


<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">What are Turkey Scholarships and Who Can Apply?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey Scholarships is a full scholarship education program awarded by the Republic of Turkey. It covers many needs such as accommodation, monthly scholarships, health insurance and language training. Students who are refugees and asylum seekers in Turkey can apply as long as they document that they are under temporary protection.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process-requirements-and-dates">Application Process, Requirements and Dates</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications are usually received in January-February each year. However, there may be additional application deadlines for some special programs (e.g. Syria Joint Scholarship Program). In 2021, applications were made between September 28 and October 15. For this reason, the <a>official website</a> must be followed.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-refugee-and-asylum-seeker-students-in-turkey-can-get-involved-in-this-program">How Refugee and Asylum Seeker Students in Turkey Can Get Involved in this Program</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students who log in to the application system can register by entering their ID numbers and temporary protection documents. Documents such as language certificate, diploma and motivation letter are required.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Turkey Scholarships Application Process Summary:</strong></p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Stage</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Application</td>
<td>Application via online system with documents</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Evaluation</td>
<td>Academic success + social situation analysis</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Interview</td>
<td>Selected Zoom or face-to-face interview</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Placement</td>
<td>University and department assignment</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Admission and Visa Process</td>
<td>Arrival and settlement in Turkey</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="spark-scholarship-program-syria-joint-program-and-frit-support">SPARK Scholarship Program: Syria Joint Program and FRIT Support</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">SPARK is a scholarship program that plays an important role especially for refugee students from Syria. It has been actively implemented since 2020 under the European Union&#8217;s Facility for Refugees in Turkey (FRIT). SPARK&#8217;s main objective is to facilitate access to university for young people under temporary protection.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-is-spark-and-who-is-it-suitable-for">What is SPARK and Who is it Suitable for?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">SPARK is a scholarship model developed especially for Syrian refugees. The aim is both to help them integrate into permanent life in Turkey and to support them in their transition to higher education. Students participating in this program receive significant support for housing, transportation and educational expenses.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="special-application-channels-for-syrian-refugees">Special Application Channels for Syrian Refugees</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">SPARK&#8217;s website and offices in Turkey allow direct applications. They also cooperate with some foundation universities and local NGOs to provide guidance to students. Applications usually open in the fall.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-documents-and-process-step-by-step">Application Documents and Process Step by Step</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are the basic documents required for the SPARK scholarship:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Temporary protection identity document</li>



<li>High school diploma or equivalency certificate</li>



<li>Motivational letter</li>



<li>Note transcript (if available)</li>



<li>Language proficiency certificate (for some departments)</li>
</ol>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">SPARK&#8217;s biggest advantage is that it supports students not only financially, but also in terms of social integration.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="ngos-providing-education-in-turkey-and-international-supporters">NGOs Providing Education in Turkey and International Supporters</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As important as government programs for refugee and asylum-seeking students in Turkey is the support provided by non-governmental organizations (NGOs) and international institutions. These organizations make a significant contribution especially in the areas of pre-university preparation, psychosocial support and cultural integration.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="role-of-unhcr-ytb-dafi-and-other-organizations">Role of UNHCR, YTB, DAFI and Other Organizations</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">UNHCR (United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees) supports the DAFI program in Turkey, which is implemented in different countries for refugee students to access university. The DAFI scholarship is a model that facilitates refugees&#8217; access to university and can cover the full cost of education.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Presidency for Turks Abroad and <a href="https://ytb.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Turks Abroad and Related Communities (YTB)</a> can work in integration with Turkey Scholarships to prioritize refugee and asylum-seeking youth, especially under the &#8220;Students with Special Situations&#8221; quota.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more information, visit <a href="https://www.unhcr.org/tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">UNHCR Turkey</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="joint-projects-and-preparatory-programs-with-universities">Joint Projects and Preparatory Programs with Universities</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many universities now collaborate with NGOs to create &#8220;Preparatory Campuses&#8221;. In these campuses, both Turkish education and cultural adaptation process are supported. </p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="social-supports-for-refugee-and-asylum-seeker-students-in-turkey">Social Supports for Refugee and Asylum Seeker Students in Turkey</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Beyond scholarships, some local municipalities also offer transportation cards, stationery assistance or food support. In densely populated provinces such as Istanbul, Gaziantep and Şanlıurfa, these supports are carried out in a more organized manner.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="institutions-providing-scholarships-for-refugee-and-asylum-seeker-students-in-turkey-table">Institutions Providing Scholarships for Refugee and Asylum Seeker Students in Turkey (Table)</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The table below summarizes the main institutions actively providing scholarships for refugee and asylum-seeking students in Turkey. Each institution has a different scope and application method, so the details should be carefully examined.</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
