<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="european-union-supported-scholarships-erasmus-jean-monnet-and-more">European Union Supported Scholarships: Erasmus+, Jean Monnet and More</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>international scholarships</strong> such as Erasmus+ and Jean Monnet are programs funded by the European Union and run in cooperation with Turkey. Not only students who want to go to Europe, but also those who want to come to Turkey from Europe can benefit from these programs.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These types of <strong>international scholarships</strong> provide not only financial support, but also the opportunity to learn about different cultures and build an international network. Erasmus Mundus partner programs stand out, especially for master&#8217;s and doctoral level students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some of the most popular EU scholarships:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Erasmus+ Student Exchange Program</strong>: Study or internship at Turkish universities for 6-12 months</li>



<li><strong>Jean Monnet Scholarship Program</strong>: Full scholarship for foreigners pursuing a master&#8217;s degree on the EU</li>



<li><strong>Horizon Europe Study Grants</strong>: Support for research-oriented master&#8217;s and doctoral students</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">The Guide to Life in Turkey for Foreign Students</a> can help you a lot in this process.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="study-in-turkey-with-islamic-development-bank-isdb-scholarships">Study in Turkey with Islamic Development Bank (IsDB) Scholarships</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Islamic Development Bank is offering special <strong>international scholarships</strong> for citizens of Muslim countries who want to study in Turkey. These scholarships cover not only education but also accommodation, health and living expenses.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is among the most preferred countries for IsDB scholars due to its cultural and religious affinity. In this way, Turkish universities are also opening their doors to more global students through <strong>international scholarships</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">IsDB&#8217;s scholarships fall into three main categories:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>University Scholarship</strong>: Full scholarships in priority fields such as medicine, engineering, agriculture</li>



<li><strong>Master&#8217;s and PhD</strong>: Provides funding for research-oriented studies</li>



<li><strong>Research and Development Grants</strong>: For post-university academic studies</li>
</ol>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Among the application requirements, the applicant must be active in both academic achievement and social responsibility. IsDB scholarships cover not only education but also accommodation, health insurance and living expenses.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Tips:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Prepare your letter of intent meticulously before applying.</li>



<li>Documenting your participation in volunteer projects gives you an advantage.</li>



<li>English proficiency certificate (IELTS/TOEFL) is required in most programs.</li>
</ul>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-fulbright-and-other-us-funded-scholarships-offer-in-turkey">What Fulbright and Other US Funded Scholarships Offer in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The first name that comes to mind when it comes to US-based <strong>international scholarships</strong> is <a href="https://www.fulbright.org.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Fulbright</a>. This scholarship program offers a full range of support for students who wish to pursue a master&#8217;s or doctoral degree in Turkey. In addition, some private American foundations also provide project-based scholarships.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Thanks to Fulbright scholarships, students studying in Turkey strengthen their academic ties with the United States and gain a prestigious label in the field of <strong>international scholarships</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Fulbright Scholarship</strong> offers:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Full tuition fee</li>



<li>Monthly living allowance</li>



<li>Health insurance</li>



<li>Flight ticket roundtrip</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In addition, various private foundations that cooperate with American universities (e.g. Ford Foundation, American Research Institute in Turkey) can also provide project-based or academic merit-based scholarships.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most of these scholarships, however, target <strong>universities</strong> that have established close academic ties with the United States. Some of the universities in Turkey are also part of this network. Therefore, you should carefully examine where the program will lead you.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="education-supports-of-international-non-governmental-organizations">Education Supports of International Non-Governmental Organizations</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>international scholarships</strong> awarded by NGOs are often aimed at minority groups, human rights defenders or young people working in the environmental field. DAAD, Chevening and Open Society Foundation are examples of such scholarships.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These <strong>international scholarships</strong> offer students not only economic support, but also a strong sense of ethical and social responsibility. There are many students studying with such scholarships in Turkey.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are some examples:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>DAAD (Germany)</strong>: Support for students studying in German-speaking departments in Turkey</li>



<li><strong>Chevening (UK)</strong>: Full scholarship for graduate students with leadership potential</li>



<li><strong>Open Society Foundation</strong>: Support for students working in areas such as minority rights, freedom of expression</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some NGO scholarships operate independently of the official application process in Turkey. However, these scholarships also require students to obtain a <strong>residence permit</strong> and often require <a class="">Health Insurance Required for Residence Permit in Turkey</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-to-consider-when-looking-for-a-scholarship-golden-tips-for-application">What to Consider When Looking for a Scholarship? Golden Tips for Application</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applying for a scholarship is an exciting but complicated process. Gathering documents, keeping track of deadlines and applying to the right place can often be confusing. Here are a few golden tips:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Personalize your Letter of Intent</strong>: Not every scholarship institution wants to see the same letter. Shape your intentions according to the program you are applying for.</li>



<li><strong>Review Previous Winners</strong>: Usually scholarship sites have profiles of people who have won scholarships in the past years. This will give you an idea. </li>



<li><strong>Stick to the Application Calendar</strong>: Application dates for some scholarships may not align with the Turkish academic calendar.</li>



<li><strong>Do you need a language certificate? IELTS or TOEFL is not always mandatory, but it is an advantage if you have it.</strong></li>



<li><strong><strong>Don&#8217;t forget the visa process</strong>: When you win the scholarship, the visa process will be waiting for you. In particular, it would be good to know in advance about the <a class="">Transition Process from Student Visa to Residence Permit in Turkey</a>.</strong></li>
</ol>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="outcome-start-exploring-your-chances-today">Outcome: Start Exploring Your Chances Today</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to study in Turkey with international scholarships, getting access to the right resources early can really make a difference. Application processes may change every year, but one thing remains constant: Well prepared wins.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Remember, <a>Road to Study</a> offers you both guidance and step-by-step support for your applications.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Now is the time to act. Scholarships are waiting for you.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">frequently asked questions</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Does Turkey offer scholarships for international students?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Turkish Scholarships program provides comprehensive support for international students pursuing undergraduate, master’s, PhD, and research programs at prestigious Turkish universities.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the 100% scholarship to study in Turkey?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Türkiye Scholarships (Turkiye Burslari) is a fully funded program covering tuition, accommodation, monthly stipend, health insurance, and a return flight ticket.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How do you qualify for the Turkish Government scholarship 2025?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Eligibility includes being under 21 (bachelor’s), 30 (master’s), 35 (PhD), or 45 (research), with minimum academic scores of 70% (bachelor’s), 75% (master’s/PhD), or 90% (health sciences).</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is the easiest fully-funded scholarship for international students?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Türkiye Scholarships are highly accessible due to no application fee, optional IELTS, and a straightforward online application process for all academic levels.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How to win a Turkey scholarship?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Apply online via turkiyeburslari.gov.tr, submit required documents, ensure strong academic records, write a compelling statement of purpose, and meet deadlines.</p>



