<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="european-union-supported-scholarships-erasmus-jean-monnet-and-more">European Union Supported Scholarships: Erasmus+, Jean Monnet and More</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>international scholarships</strong> such as Erasmus+ and Jean Monnet are programs funded by the European Union and run in cooperation with Turkey. Not only students who want to go to Europe, but also those who want to come to Turkey from Europe can benefit from these programs.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These types of <strong>international scholarships</strong> provide not only financial support, but also the opportunity to learn about different cultures and build an international network. Erasmus Mundus partner programs stand out, especially for master&#8217;s and doctoral level students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some of the most popular EU scholarships:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Erasmus+ Student Exchange Program</strong>: Study or internship at Turkish universities for 6-12 months</li>



<li><strong>Jean Monnet Scholarship Program</strong>: Full scholarship for foreigners pursuing a master&#8217;s degree on the EU</li>



<li><strong>Horizon Europe Study Grants</strong>: Support for research-oriented master&#8217;s and doctoral students</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Also, <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/">The Guide to Life in Turkey for Foreign Students</a> can help you a lot in this process.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="study-in-turkey-with-islamic-development-bank-isdb-scholarships">Study in Turkey with Islamic Development Bank (IsDB) Scholarships</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Islamic Development Bank is offering special <strong>international scholarships</strong> for citizens of Muslim countries who want to study in Turkey. These scholarships cover not only education but also accommodation, health and living expenses.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Turkey is among the most preferred countries for IsDB scholars due to its cultural and religious affinity. In this way, Turkish universities are also opening their doors to more global students through <strong>international scholarships</strong>.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">IsDB&#8217;s scholarships fall into three main categories:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>University Scholarship</strong>: Full scholarships in priority fields such as medicine, engineering, agriculture</li>



<li><strong>Master&#8217;s and PhD</strong>: Provides funding for research-oriented studies</li>



<li><strong>Research and Development Grants</strong>: For post-university academic studies</li>
</ol>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Among the application requirements, the applicant must be active in both academic achievement and social responsibility. IsDB scholarships cover not only education but also accommodation, health insurance and living expenses.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Tips:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Prepare your letter of intent meticulously before applying.</li>



<li>Documenting your participation in volunteer projects gives you an advantage.</li>



<li>English proficiency certificate (IELTS/TOEFL) is required in most programs.</li>
</ul>


