<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="who-can-apply-basic-terms-and-requirements">Who Can Apply? Basic Terms and Requirements</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Although each scholarship has its own criteria, <strong>embassy and consulate scholarships</strong> generally require a certain age range, GPA and language proficiency.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-age-limits-and-academic-success-requirements">Application Age Limits and Academic Success Requirements</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For example, there is usually an age limit of 25 for an undergraduate student applying for a Fulbright scholarship, while Japan&#8217;s MEXT scholarships give preference to 18-22 year olds. You are also expected to meet the academic requirements of the program you are applying to: usually a minimum 70% pass rate is required.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="language-proficiency-and-document-preparation">Language Proficiency and Document Preparation</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Since most scholarships are offered in English or the official language of the respective country, documents such as TOEFL, IELTS or JLPT are required. In addition, documents such as CV, reference letter, motivation letter are the most important parts of the application file.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process-from-consulates-to-universities">Application Process: From Consulates to Universities</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>The application process for embassy and consulate scholarships</strong> varies from country to country, but the basic steps are generally similar:</p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li>Follow announcements</li>



<li>Prepare your documents</li>



<li>Contact the embassy</li>



<li>Join the interview</li>



<li>Wait for results</li>
</ol>



