<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Ahiler Agency&#8217;s support for 2025 includes funding for university clubs. Entrepreneurship and cultural exchange clubs, where foreign students are especially active, had the chance to realize their own projects with this support.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="serhat-development-agencys-language-oriented-projects">Serhat Development Agency&#8217;s Language Oriented Projects</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Serhat Development Agency provided instructional materials and digital resources for foreign language education at universities in the border region. In addition, &#8220;Intercultural Communication&#8221; seminars at Kafkas University were supported by development agency funds.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="who-can-benefit-application-requirements-and-process">Who Can Benefit? Application Requirements and Process</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There is no requirement to be a Turkish citizen. Since some support programs are implemented through universities or civil society organizations rather than directly through individuals, it is possible for international students to be involved in these projects. Support can be utilized especially through volunteer work, student organizations and research projects.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="eligibility-criteria-for-international-students">Eligibility Criteria for International Students</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each development agency determines a strategy specific to its region. However, in general, students who are active in education-related social responsibility projects, take part in university clubs or contribute to academic projects can be included in the scope of support.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-documents-and-process-steps">Application Documents and Process Steps</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications are usually made through the official websites of the agencies. Required documents include an application form, a project idea summary and a letter of support. In case of project partnership, approval letters from the club or university advisor may also be required.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="distribution-of-education-support-by-region">Distribution of Education Support by Region</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Since not all regions of Turkey have the same needs, agencies are developing different training projects based on regional priorities. See some of the featured agencies and programs in the table below.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="incentive-advantages-in-eastern-and-southeastern-anatolia">Incentive Advantages in Eastern and Southeastern Anatolia</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Social development projects are prioritized in these regions. Serhat, Karacadağ and Dicle Development Agencies focus especially on vocational training and cultural integration programs. You can work as a volunteer or part-time in projects supported by these agencies.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="project-examples-in-thrace-and-black-sea-regions">Project Examples in Thrace and Black Sea Regions</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The Thracian Development Agency stands out with examples of foreign students working with Turkish students on joint social responsibility projects. In the Black Sea region, the Eastern Black Sea Development Agency (DOKA) provides support for tourism training and cultural promotion projects.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="education-supports-regional-breakdown">Education Supports &#8211; Regional Breakdown</h3>


