<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="other-civil-society-organizations-and-education-support-in-turkey">Other Civil Society Organizations and Education Support in Turkey</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Each year, hundreds of local and national <strong>civil society</strong> organizations contribute to the educational journey of university students by providing scholarships. Some are active only in certain provinces, while others are open to applications throughout Turkey. Since these organizations work more flexibly than official procedures, they can have one-to-one contact with students, which is an important advantage in the application process.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="supports-provided-by-local-associations-and-foundations">Supports Provided by Local Associations and Foundations</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some local foundations and associations offer scholarships specifically for universities in their region. These scholarships usually take the form of monthly cash assistance, food or housing support.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Izmir Education Foundation:</strong> Provides scholarships for Ege University students, giving priority to engineering and health departments.</li>



<li><strong>Anadolu Education and Culture Foundation:</strong> It aims to provide equal opportunities by reaching out to students from the eastern provinces.</li>



<li><strong>Istanbul Education and Youth Association:</strong> Offers monthly support to students who commit to volunteer in cultural projects.</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Such <strong>civil society</strong> initiatives contribute not only to the financial, but also to the social and cultural development of students.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="special-scholarships-for-women-students-disabled-individuals-and-refugees">Special Scholarships for Women Students, Disabled Individuals and Refugees</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Adopting values such as gender equality, accessibility and social inclusion, <strong>civil society</strong> organizations draw attention with their scholarship programs especially for disadvantaged groups.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Feminist organizations such as Mor Çatı, which supports women students, provide not only financial, but also psychological and social support. Associations for students with disabilities provide scholarships as well as educational material support.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarships for refugee and asylum-seeking students are often internationally funded and contribute greatly to the integration of migrants into the education system.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">👉 For more details: <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Special Scholarship Opportunities for Women Students in Turkey</a></p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-apply-for-a-scholarship-step-by-step-guide">How to Apply for a Scholarship? Step by Step Guide</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applying for a scholarship can seem daunting at first glance, but if you know the right steps, it can be a lot easier. NGO scholarship programs are usually opened at certain times of the year and applications are accepted through online forms.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-documents-deadlines-and-things-to-consider">Application Documents, Deadlines and Things to Consider</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are the basic documents most NGOs require:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Current transcript</li>



<li>Documents showing the income status of the family (payslip, SSI breakdown)</li>



<li>Population register sample</li>



<li>Motivational letter</li>



<li>At least one letter of reference</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Some scholarships may also ask about a student&#8217;s volunteering history or involvement in social projects. So don&#8217;t just fill out the application form, but be clear about what makes you different.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Note:</strong> Don&#8217;t miss the deadlines! Many applications close in September and October. A regular calendar would be very helpful in this regard.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">👉 For more application tips: <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Common Mistakes in Scholarship Applications in Turkey</a></p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading" id="motivation-letter-and-reference-writing-tips">Motivation Letter and Reference Writing Tips</h4>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you find it difficult to explain yourself, you are not alone. But remember, the organizations you are applying to are interested in human stories, not numbers. In your motivational letter, consider answering these questions:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>What will this scholarship change in your life? </li>



<li>What social contribution are you aiming for?</li>



<li>What are your future plans? </li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For a letter of recommendation, ask a teacher or counselor who really believes in you. Avoid stereotypes; personal and sincere language should be preferred.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="now-is-the-time-to-apply-take-the-first-step-to-realize-your-dream">Now is the Time to Apply: Take the First Step to Realize Your Dream</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Scholarships are not only financial support; they are also a sign of trust. It extends a hand that says &#8220;You are valuable&#8221;. NGO scholarships offer this support from the heart. Applying is the first step to success.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you are currently studying or planning to study in Turkey, don&#8217;t miss these opportunities. With the right information, the right timing and well-prepared documents, you too can win a scholarship.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Act now!</strong> There is a scholarship in Turkey that will support you. And remember, <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a> is ready to be your companion in your scholarship search.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-08-05T14:04:53Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T19:22:59Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/scholarships-provided-by-civil-society-organizations-in-turkey.webp","alt":"Scholarships by civil society organizations in Turkey","title":"scholarships-provided-by-civil-society-organizations-in-turkey"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'civil-society-scholarships' );
