<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In Turkey, religious foundations offer attractive opportunities for students from Africa, Central Asia and the Balkans. Although these scholarships are generally aimed at those studying in departments such as Theology, Social Sciences, Educational Sciences, etc., they have also started to be opened to some technical fields.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For those who want to gain internship and work experience in different fields, you can check our guide on <a class="">Financial Support for Internships and Work Experience in Turkey</a>.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="who-can-apply-which-documents-are-required">Who can apply? Which Documents are Required?</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Applications are usually received in the spring of each year and the following documents are required:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Required Document</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Passport Photocopy</td>
<td>Must be valid for more than 6 months</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Graduation Certificate</td>
<td>High school diploma or equivalent</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Transcript</td>
<td>Note </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Letter of Reference</td>
<td>Must be from an academic or religious authority</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Letter of Intent</td>
<td>Must describe educational goals and religious motivation</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>


<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="application-process-and-evaluation-criteria">Application Process and Evaluation Criteria</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">In the evaluation phase, not only academic achievement is important, but also the candidate&#8217;s level of religious knowledge, cultural compatibility and sense of social responsibility. <strong>Religious foundations</strong> in Turkey can be said to be looking for &#8220;role model&#8221; potential in students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more information on this process, you can also check our article <a class="">Points to Consider When Applying for a Scholarship in Turkey</a>.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="educational-institutions-and-housing-support">Educational Institutions and Housing Support</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>In Turkey, religious foundations</strong> not only provide scholarships, but also meet the physical needs of students. A student&#8217;s needs such as housing, food and stationery are just as important as tuition.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="medrasas-theology-faculties-and-academic-circles">Medrasas, Theology Faculties and Academic Circles</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Today, modern faculties of theology and traditional madrasa systems go hand in hand. The Diyanet Foundation of Turkey works in cooperation with these institutions in cities such as Istanbul, Konya and Bursa. In addition, some foundations have established private theological schools.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These institutions are not limited to religious education. Logic, philosophy, Arabic and even English are taught in some foundations. Thus, students are supported in terms of both religious and intellectual development.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="hostel-food-stationery-and-clothing-aids">Hostel, Food, Stationery and Clothing Aids</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>Religious foundations</strong> in Turkey also offer students significant opportunities in terms of housing. Foundation dormitories offer free or symbolic meals. Some dormitories offer three meals during the week and a weekend breakfast buffet.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The organization also provides winter clothing, books and notebooks once a year. TDV&#8217;s traditional &#8220;student dressing&#8221; activities provide great comfort, especially during the winter months.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="advantages-and-limits-of-studying-with-religious-support-in-turkey">Advantages and Limits of Studying with Religious Support in Turkey</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For a student from abroad, Turkey is a country that is religiously and culturally familiar, but also full of novelty. <strong>Religious foundations</strong> in Turkey facilitate adaptation by providing both moral and financial support to students during this transition.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="factors-facilitating-cultural-adaptation">Factors Facilitating Cultural Adaptation</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Students staying in foundation dormitories are often together with individuals from similar cultural backgrounds. Common prayer times, conversation circles, and book reading activities help develop language and cultural cohesion.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For many students, these environments can feel like a &#8220;family far away&#8221;. Especially in the first year, this support makes a huge difference.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="apply-today-get-support-tomorrow-take-action">Apply Today, Get Support Tomorrow &#8211; Take Action!</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong>In Turkey, religious foundations</strong> are among the architects not only of the past but also of the future. These foundations are an ideal support point for students who want to preserve their religious identity and receive quality academic education.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Remember, applications are taken at certain times of the year and the quota is limited. If your documents are ready and you are eligible, do not hesitate to apply now.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">For more information, to request an individual consultation or to have your documents checked, visit <a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">RoadToStudy&#8217;s homepage</a>.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2025-08-05T14:03:46Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-15T19:23:00Z', '$.featured_image', json('{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/educational-support-provided-by-religious-foundations-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"Educational support by religious foundations in Türkiye","title":"educational-support-provided-by-religious-foundations-in-turkiye"}')) WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'educational-support-from-religious-foundations' );
