Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarships-provided-by-alumni-associations-in-turkiye.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarships-provided-by-alumni-associations-in-turkiye.webp","width":"2336","height":"1760","caption":"Scholarships from alumni associations in Turkiye","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/alumni-association-scholarships/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/alumni-association-scholarships/","name":"Alumni Association Support in Turkey: 9-Month Scholarships","datePublished":"2025-08-05T17:08:37+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:58+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarships-provided-by-alumni-associations-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Alumni Association Support in Turkey: 9-Month Scholarships","keywords":"alumni association","datePublished":"2025-08-05T17:08:37+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-15T22:22:58+03:00","articleSection":"Scholarships and Funding","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Make being a student in Turkey easier with scholarships from alumni associations like GSUMED, METU, and CYDD. Apply and don&#039;t miss this opportunity!","name":"Alumni Association Support in Turkey: 9-Month Scholarships","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/alumni-association-scholarships/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/alumni-association-scholarships/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarships-provided-by-alumni-associations-in-turkiye.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/alumni-association-scholarships/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As an aspiring student in Turkey, scholarships are perhaps one of the most critical things you think about. Although not as well known as state scholarships or private foundation support, &#8220;<strong>alumni association</strong>&#8221; scholarships can also make a difference in university life. Based on their own experiences, alumni see it as a responsibility to support the next generation of students and organize this in a serious way. Especially the alumni associations of big universities are very active and generous in this regard.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<h2 id="mezunlar-dernegi-nedir-ve-neden-onem önemlidir" class="wp-block-heading"> </h2>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">What is Alumni Association and Why is it Important?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These associations also function as active fundraisers and provide support to students. Scholarship funds are created, sometimes with the support of a single graduate, sometimes with the contributions of dozens of graduates. These scholarships are also directed directly to students in need.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-association-culture-in-turkey-and-its-place-in-education">The Association Culture in Turkey and its Place in Education</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Especially at the university level, alumni associations of institutions provide both financial assistance and mentorship to students. Associations are a powerful source of not only financial but also social capital. Alumni can support students with internships, jobs and even housing. At a time when access to affordable living spaces such as <a class="">student-friendly restaurants and dining halls</a> is crucial in Turkey, this kind of support is golden.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="the-most-known-alumni-association-scholarships-in-turkey">The Most Known Alumni Association Scholarships in Turkey</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="gsumed-scholarship-program-galatasaray-university">GSUAA Scholarship Program &#8211; Galatasaray University</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://gsumed.org/burs-programi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Galatasaray University Alumni Association (GSUAA)</a> provides scholarships to students in need every year. This scholarship is paid regularly for 9 months and aims to reduce the financial burden students face during their education. The application requirements are announced on GSUAA&#8217;s official website and are usually updated at the beginning of each academic year. Especially social sciences students benefit intensively from this scholarship.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="odtu-alumni-association-scholarship-and-aids-committee">METU Alumni Association &#8211; Scholarship and Aids Committee</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://www.odtumd.org.tr/burs-ve-yardimlar-komitesi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The METU Alumni Association</a>, based in Ankara, provides scholarships to hundreds of students every year. The scholarship amounts for the 2024-2025 academic year are approximately <strong>59 USD</strong> for a full scholarship and <strong>36 USD</strong> for a half scholarship. The application process is very organized. Students must apply to the association with a transcript, student certificate and a statement of financial situation. These applications are usually received in <strong>September</strong> and the evaluation process is meticulously carried out.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="association-for-supporting-contemporary-life">Association for Supporting Contemporary Life</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Although not an &#8220;alumni association&#8221;, <a href="https://www.cydd.org.tr/sayfa/universite-burslari-104/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CYDD</a> serves a similar function with its scholarship projects supported by alumni donations. Hundreds of students have been supported for years thanks to scholarships given through institutions such as Hergüner Bilgen Özeke Law Office or Aresk Kimya. Students who apply for these scholarships are generally individuals with low socioeconomic status but high academic achievement.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here is a brief summary of these scholarships in a table:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th><strong>Alumni Association</strong></th>
<th><strong>Scholarship Type</strong></th>
<th><strong>Term</strong></th>
<th><strong>Amount (Monthly)</strong></th>
<th><strong>Application Time</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>GSUAA</td>
<td>Support Scholarship</td>
<td>9 Months</td>
<td>40-60 USD (variable)</td>
<td>September-October</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ODTU Alumni Association</td>
<td>Full/Half</td>
<td>9 Months</td>
<td>36 USD / 59 USD</td>
<td>September</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ÇYDD</td>
<td>Project Scholarship</td>
<td>Variable</td>
<td>30-70 USD (donation dependent)</td>
<td>Full year</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</figure>
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="how-to-apply-for-alumni-association-scholarships">How to Apply for Alumni Association Scholarships</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="documents-online-forms-and-references">Documents, Online Forms and References</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Although each &#8220;<strong>alumni association</strong>&#8221; scholarship requires different documents, the following are generally required: student certificate, transcript, proof of income and a short motivational letter. Some associations ask you to fill in an online form, while others receive applications by e-mail. Letters of reference are a big plus.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="dates-and-details-to-watch-out-for">Dates and Details to Watch Out For</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Application deadlines vary from association to association. It usually opens in early September and lasts about a month. It is very important to pay attention to the deadline and submit the documents in full and on time. Otherwise, the application will not be evaluated.</p>


<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" />
<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height: 22px;" aria-hidden="true"> </div>
<h2 id="yabanci-ogrenciler-icin-mezunlar-dernegi-burslari-mumkun-mu" class="wp-block-heading"> </h2>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading wp-block-paragraph">Is Alumni Association Scholarships for Foreign Students Possible?</h2>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="eligibility-requirements-and-language-barrier">Eligibility Requirements and Language Barrier</h3>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Most <strong>alumni association</strong> scholarship programs in Turkey are predominantly aimed at Turkish citizens. This is mainly because the donor networks of the associations are usually made up of local alumni. However, this does not always mean &#8220;no&#8221;. Some special scholarship programs may also be open to foreign students, especially for projects related to international relations, cultural exchange or social responsibility.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The language barrier should also be taken into account. Applications are usually made in Turkish. Therefore, getting support from a Turkish friend or advisor when filling out the application form can make your job easier. Also, writing your motivation letter in Turkish can help the evaluators get to know you better.</p>


<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>
<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" >
<div style="height:22px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="apply-for-alumni-association-scholarship-and-make-a-difference">Apply for Alumni Association Scholarship and Make a Difference</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Sometimes a little support is the first step towards a big change. Scholarships from <strong>alumni associations</strong> in Turkey are not only about financial aid, but also about a sense of belonging and solidarity. A student who applies for a scholarship today may be the supporting graduate of tomorrow.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">All you need to do is find the right organization, prepare your application documents and step into the process with courage. Especially in the first years of university life, such scholarships can provide you with both economic and psychological relief. So now is the time to act.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a class="" href="https://roadtostudy.com">Road to Study</a> would like to be with you every step of your educational journey. Be sure to check the official page of the university and the announcements of the alumni association before applying. Push your luck, because no scholarship is won without applying! </p>', "wp_published_at" = '2025-08-05T14:08:37Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-15T19:22:58Z', "featured_image" = '{"provider":"external","src":"/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/scholarships-provided-by-alumni-associations-in-turkiye.webp","alt":"Scholarships from alumni associations in Turkiye","title":"scholarships-provided-by-alumni-associations-in-turkiye"}' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'alumni-association-scholarships';
